name: Time.Extra

values.name: addDays
values.comment:
Adds 24 hours to a Posix. Note that this function does not account for
daylight savings time.

Maybe you want the addDaysZ function?

values.name: addDaysZ
values.comment: Adds 24 hours to a `Posix`, attempting to correct for daylight savings time.

values.name: addHours
values.comment: Add the given hours to the `Posix` time.

values.name: addMillis
values.comment: Add the given milliseconds to the `Posix` time.

values.name: addMinutes
values.comment: Add the given minutes to the `Posix` time.

values.name: addSeconds
values.comment: Add the given seconds to the `Posix` time.

values.name: anteMeridiem
values.comment: Does the given `Posix` occure in the morning of a given `Zone`?

values.name: compare
values.comment: Compares one `Posix` time to another.

values.name: daysInMonth
values.comment: The number of days in a given year and month.

values.name: endOfDay
values.comment: Set the `Posix` to the end of the day in a given `Zone`.

values.name: endOfHour
values.comment: Set the `Posix` to the end of the hour in a given `Zone`.

values.name: endOfMonth
values.comment: Set the `Posix` to the end of the month in a given `Zone`.

values.name: endOfWeek
values.comment:
Set the `Posix` to the end of the week in a given `Zone` and the start of the
week (a `Weekday`).

values.name: fromDateTuple
values.comment: Converts a date tuple (year, month, day) to a `Posix` for a given `Zone`.

values.name: fromIso8601Date
values.comment: Converts an ISO8601 date into a`Posix` for a given `Zone`.

values.name: intToMonth
values.comment: Convert an `Int` to a `Month`, with January being 1.

values.name: monthToInt
values.comment: Convert a `Month` to an `Int`, with January being 1.

values.name: setDay
values.comment:
Set the day of month for a given `Zone`. If the given day is greater then the
number of days in the month it is set to the last day of the month.

values.name: setHour
values.comment: Set the hour of a `Posix` given a `Zone`.

values.name: setMillis
values.comment: Set the milliseconds of a `Posix` given a `Zone`.

values.name: setMinute
values.comment: Set the minutes of a `Posix` given a `Zone`.

values.name: setMonth
values.comment: Set the month of a `Posix` time for a given `Zone`.

values.name: setSecond
values.comment: Set the seconds of a `Posix` given a `Zone`.

values.name: setYear
values.comment: Set the year of a `Posix` time for a given `Zone`.

values.name: startOfDay
values.comment: Set the `Posix` to the start of the day in a given `Zone`.

values.name: startOfHour
values.comment: Set the `Posix` to the start of the hour in a given `Zone`.

values.name: startOfMonth
values.comment: Set the `Posix` to the start of the month in a given `Zone`.

values.name: startOfWeek
values.comment:
Set the `Posix` to the start of the week in a given `Zone` and the start of the
week (a `Weekday`).

values.name: toDateTuple
values.comment: Converts a `Posix` into a date tuple (year, month, day) for a given `Zone`

values.name: toIso8601Date
values.comment: Converts a `Posix` into an ISO8601 date for a given `Zone`

values.name: toIso8601DateTime
values.comment: Converts a `Posix` into an ISO8601 date and time for a given `Zone`

values.name: toIso8601DateTimeUTC
values.comment: Converts a `Posix` into an ISO8601 date and time in UTC

values.name: toIso8601Time
values.comment: Converts a `Posix` into an ISO8601 time for a given `Zone`

values.name: toTimeTuple
values.comment: Converts a `Posix` into a time tuple (hour, minute, second) for a given `Zone`

values.name: weekdayFromInt
values.comment: Convert an `Int` to a `Weekday`, with Monday being 1 and Sunday being 7.

values.name: weekdayToInt
values.comment: Convert a `Weekday` to an `Int`, with Monday being 1 and Sunday being 7.
